CHILD OBSERVATIONS (CULTURE FOCUS)

9:45 AM - Oscar (4) chose the Continent Puzzle Map. He's done this before. Built it quickly (maybe 5 minutes). Called me over to show me. Asked "What's this blue part?" (Indian Ocean). We talked about oceans vs continents. He wanted to find animals that live in each continent. Connected to our animal matching cards. Good cross-material thinking.

10:00 AM - Sophia (4.5) working with globe. Spinning it, looking at different countries. Asked which country is biggest (Russia). Showed her. She wanted to know what people eat there. I don't know much about Russian food honestly - told her we could look it up later. Note to self: Get some culture books about different countries for reference.

10:15 AM - Emma (5) and Zoe (5) working together on Continent Animal Matching cards. Taking turns placing animals. Emma knows a lot - has been working with this material for weeks. Teaching Zoe. "Pandas live in Asia because that's where bamboo grows." Good peer teaching happening.

10:30 AM - Lucas (5) at Parts of a Plant booklet (three-part cards). Matching labels to pictures. Getting them all correct. Focused work for about 15 minutes. Then moved to looking at real plant we have in classroom (spider plant) and identifying parts - roots, stem, leaves. Applying knowledge to real world. Perfect.

10:45 AM - Mia (3) chose the Landforms (land/water forms) from sensorial. She's still young for the culture curriculum but this is a good introduction. Island, lake, peninsula - she can make them with water and see the shapes. Good concrete foundation for later geography work.

11:00 AM - Chloe (4.5) chose art project - drawing a map of her neighborhood. This was her idea, not something I assigned. She drew her house, school, park. Used actual map vocabulary - "streets" "buildings". The culture curriculum is sparking her interest in maps generally. Good connection.

