CULTURE CURRICULUM INTEGRATION

Seeing kids make connections between:
- Geography (maps, globes, continents)
- Biology (animals, plants, habitats)
- Social studies (people in different places)

This is what culture area should do - connect everything together. Not just memorizing continent names, but understanding the world is big and diverse with different people, animals, plants, ways of living.

Today's observations show kids are starting to get this bigger picture.

---

MATERIALS USAGE

Popular: Animal matching cards, continent puzzle, globe
Medium use: Plant parts, landforms
Not used today: Flags (need to make these more accessible)

The materials I made myself (animal cards) are getting more use than the official purchased materials. Interesting. Kids respond to what's clear and engaging.

