TEACHER ROLE TODAY

Did two presentations:
1. Parts of Flower (new material) to Emma - she got it quickly
2. Review of continent names with Oscar - he keeps confusing North and South America

Otherwise mostly observation and minimal guidance. Answered questions when asked. Redirected a couple kids who were wandering aimlessly.

Joined Sophia at the globe when she asked about Russia. Turned into a 10-minute geography lesson about size of countries, how maps show the world flat but it's actually round. She was interested.

