OVERALL ASSESSMENT

Morning was productive. Culture area is active and kids are engaged. Seeing good use of materials and genuine learning happening.

The culture curriculum at this age (3-6) is really about opening kids' eyes to the fact that the world is bigger than their immediate environment. Different animals, plants, people, places exist. We live on a planet with many different parts.

My kids are getting this message. They're curious. They ask questions. They want to know more.

That's the goal of culture education at this level. Fostering curiosity about the world. We're doing it.

